\f2\b \cf2 1. Introduction
\f0\b0 \'a0\
We are pleased to announce that PlushCare, Inc., PlushCare of California, Inc., Accolade 2ndMD LLC, and Accolade, Inc. are now part of Accolade, Inc.\'a0\
\'a0\
The use of PlushCare, Inc., PlushCare of California, Inc., Accolade 2ndMD LLC, and/or Accolade, Inc. services are subject to all of their respective terms, agreements, statements of rights, consent forms, and policies, which applied when you engaged with the respective services. When visiting an Accolade, Inc. website or using the PlushCare Services, your information will be shared, where legally permissible, with our parent company, Accolade, Inc., in accordance with the Accolade, Inc. Privacy Policy.\'a0\
\'a0\
PlushCare, Inc. and PlushCare of California, Inc., P.C. (\'93PlushCare\'94, \'93we\'94, \'93us\'94, or \'93our\'94) delivers virtual primary care and mental health treatment to its members in a high quality, convenient and affordable way. The PlushCare Privacy Policy applies to any registered users (\'93Members\'94) of our site, as well as any visitors (\'93non-members\'94).\'a0\
\'a0\
PlushCare takes your privacy seriously. This Privacy Policy applies to PlushCare -owned websites, PlushCare -branded mobile app (collectively, the \'93Sites\'94), and all communications and services offered by PlushCare (\'93Services\'94) but excludes services which state that they are offered under a different privacy policy.\'a0\'a0\
\'a0\
To best explain your rights and our obligations under this Privacy Policy, we have included more information about your rights and our obligations below, along with definitions for key terms that we use throughout the Policy. If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, you can contact us at: legal@accolade.com\'a0\
\'a0\
This Privacy Policy is incorporated into, and is subject to, the\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://plushcare.com/terms/"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 Terms of Use.}}
\f3 \uc0\u8239 
\f0  By using the Sites and the Services, you accept and agree to the practices described in this Privacy Policy. Capitalized terms used in this Privacy Policy and not defined herein shall have the definitions provided in our Terms of Use.\'a0\
\'a0\
Please read this privacy notice carefully as it will help you understand what we do with the information that we collect.\'a0\'a0\
\'a0\

\f2\b 2. Privacy Policy Change
\f0\b0 \'a0\
PlushCare reserves the right to modify, expand, or remove portions of this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any and all changes to this Privacy Policy will be reflected here and the date new versions are posted will be stated at the bottom of this Privacy Policy. Your continued use of the Sites and the Services indicates your agreement with these modifications and updates. If you do not agree with the changes, then you should stop using the Sites and the Services and notify us that you do not want your Personal Information used in accordance with the changes. If we make significant material changes in the way we handle Personal Information, we will send a notice to you at the email address that we have on file and/or by posting a prominent notice on the Sites.\'a0\
\'a0\

\f2\b Changes to the Accolade Digital Tools Mobile Application (\'93App\'94)
\f0\b0 \'a0\uc0\u8232 From time to time and without prior notice to you, we may change, expand, and improve the App. We may also, at any time, cease to continue operating part or all of the App or selectively disable certain features of the App. Your use of the App does not entitle you to the continued provision or availability of the App. Any modification or elimination of the App or any particular feature will be done in our sole and absolute discretion and without an ongoing obligation or liability to you.\'a0\
\'a0\

\f2\b Personal Information.
\f0\b0 \'a0When referred to in this Privacy Policy, the term \'93Personal Information\'94 includes any information that identifies, relates to, describes, is reasonably capable of being associated with, or could reasonably be linked, directly or indirectly, with a particular individual or household, including any information that is subject to applicable data protection laws.
\f3 \uc0\u8239 
\f0  Personal Information may include \'93Personal Information\'94 as defined under the California Consumer Privacy Act, Cal. Civ. Code \'a7\'a7 1798.100 et. seq., as amended (\'93CCPA\'94).\'a0\'a0\
\'a0\

\f2\b Protected Health Information.
\f0\b0 \'a0PlushCare is also committed to protecting the privacy of your protected health information (\'93Protected Health Information\'94). \'93Protected Health Information\'94 is a subset of Personal Information that is information about you, including demographic information, that may identify you and that relates to your past, present or future physical or mental health or condition; related health care services; or related to the past, present, or future payment for the provision of health care to you.\'a0 For a description of how we may use and disclose your Protected Health Information to carry out treatment, payment or health care operations and for other purposes that are permitted or required by law, including the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act of 1996 (\'93HIPAA\'94), please refer to our
\f3 \uc0\u8239 
\f4\i\b HIPAA Notice of Privacy Practices, which is available
\f5 \uc0\u8239 {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://plushcare.com/hipaa-notice-of-privacy-practices/"}}{\fldrslt 
\f4 \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 here}}
\f0\i0\b0 .
\f3 \uc0\u8239 
\f0  Any conflict between this Privacy Policy and the HIPAA Notice of Privacy Practices with respect to such submitted Protected Health Information shall be governed by the HIPAA Notice of Privacy Practices.\'a0\
\'a0\

